Sentencas: Sr0.92Y0.08Ti1-xNixO3-delta (SYTN) was investigated in the presence of H2S containing fuels to assess the feasibility of employing oxide materials as alternative anodes.
Titulo: H2S tolerance effects of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ modification on Sr0.92Y0.08Ti1-xNixO3-δ anode in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Aliovalent substitution of Ni2+ into Ti4+ increased the ionic conductivity of perovskite, leading to improved electrochemical performance of the SYTN anode.
Titulo: H2S tolerance effects of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ modification on Sr0.92Y0.08Ti1-xNixO3-δ anode in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power densities were 32.4 and 45.3 mW/cm(2) in H-2 at 900 degrees C for the SYT anode and the SYTN anode, respectively.
Titulo: H2S tolerance effects of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ modification on Sr0.92Y0.08Ti1-xNixO3-δ anode in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, the maximum power densities in 300 ppm of H2S decreased by 7% and by 46% in the SYT and the SYTN anodes, respectively.
Titulo: H2S tolerance effects of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ modification on Sr0.92Y0.08Ti1-xNixO3-δ anode in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: To enhance the sulfur tolerance and to improve the electrochemical properties, the surface of SYTN anode was modified with samarium doped ceria (SDC) using the sol-gel coating method.
Titulo: H2S tolerance effects of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ modification on Sr0.92Y0.08Ti1-xNixO3-δ anode in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For the SDC-modified SYTN anode, the cell performance was mostly recovered in the pure H-2 condition after 500-ppm H2S exposure in contrast to the irreversible cell performance degradation exhibited in the unmodified SYTN anode.
Titulo: H2S tolerance effects of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ modification on Sr0.92Y0.08Ti1-xNixO3-δ anode in solid oxide fuel cells
